<Layout title="Privacy Policy — stepIQ">
  <div class="landing">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="header">
      <a href="/" class="brand">
        <span class="logo-icon">⚡</span>
        stepIQ
      </a>
      <nav class="nav-links">
        <a href="/#features">Features</a>
        <a href="/#pricing">Pricing</a>
        <a href="/docs">Docs</a>
      </nav>
      <div class="actions">
        <a href="https://app.stepiq.sh" class="ghost-link">Log in</a>
        <a href="https://app.stepiq.sh" class="solid-link">Get Started</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="legal-page">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: February 25, 2026</p>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
        <p>stepIQ is a product of <strong>Ligerian Labs</strong>, a brand of Pupuce CORP (EURL), registered in France. We operate the websites <code>stepiq.sh</code>, <code>app.stepiq.sh</code>, and <code>api.stepiq.sh</code>.</p>
        <p><strong>Contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:bonjour@ligerianlabs.fr">bonjour@ligerianlabs.fr</a></p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Data we collect</h2>
        <h3>Account data</h3>
        <p>When you create an account, we collect your email address and a hashed version of your password. We never store plaintext passwords.</p>
        <h3>Pipeline data</h3>
        <p>We store your pipeline definitions, execution logs, step outputs, and associated metadata. This data is necessary to provide the service.</p>
        <h3>Usage data</h3>
        <p>We collect anonymized analytics data including page views, feature usage, and performance metrics to improve the product. We use PostHog (EU-hosted) for this purpose.</p>
        <h3>Payment data</h3>
        <p>If you subscribe to a paid plan, payment processing is handled by our payment provider. We do not store your full credit card details.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. How we use your data</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To provide and maintain the stepIQ service</li>
          <li>To execute your AI pipelines by sending prompts to third-party model providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Meta via inference partners)</li>
          <li>To track credit usage and billing</li>
          <li>To send transactional emails (account confirmation, password reset, usage alerts)</li>
          <li>To improve the product based on aggregated, anonymized usage patterns</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>4. Third-party model providers</h2>
        <p>When you run a pipeline, your prompts and inputs are sent to the AI model provider you selected (e.g., Anthropic, OpenAI). Each provider has its own data processing terms:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Anthropic</strong> — API inputs are not used for training. See <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anthropic's privacy policy</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>OpenAI</strong> — API inputs are not used for training by default. See <a href="https://openai.com/policies/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenAI's privacy policy</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Meta Llama</strong> — Served via inference partners. Data handling depends on the partner.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We recommend not including sensitive personal data in pipeline prompts unless you understand the downstream provider's data handling practices.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
        <p>We use strictly necessary cookies for authentication (JWT session tokens). We use PostHog for analytics, which may set cookies for session tracking. No advertising cookies are used.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
        <p>Account data is retained for the lifetime of your account. Pipeline execution logs are retained for 90 days on the Free plan and 1 year on paid plans. You can request deletion of your data at any time.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Your rights (GDPR)</h2>
        <p>If you are in the European Economic Area, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> — Request a copy of your personal data</li>
          <li><strong>Rectification</strong> — Correct inaccurate data</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — Request deletion of your data</li>
          <li><strong>Portability</strong> — Export your pipeline definitions and data</li>
          <li><strong>Object</strong> — Object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
          <li><strong>Restriction</strong> — Request limitation of processing</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:bonjour@ligerianlabs.fr">bonjour@ligerianlabs.fr</a>. We will respond within 30 days.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>8. Data security</h2>
        <p>We use industry-standard security measures including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>TLS encryption for all data in transit</li>
          <li>AES-256-GCM encryption for stored secrets and API keys</li>
          <li>Bcrypt password hashing</li>
          <li>Infrastructure hosted in European data centers</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes via email or in-app notification. Continued use of the service after changes constitutes acceptance.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>10. Contact</h2>
        <p>For any questions about this privacy policy or your data, contact us at:</p>
        <p><strong>Ligerian Labs (Pupuce CORP EURL)</strong><br/>
        Email: <a href="mailto:bonjour@ligerianlabs.fr">bonjour@ligerianlabs.fr</a><br/>
        Angers, France</p>
      </section>
    </main>

